  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>1.&amp;nbsp;Approach&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    Describe the approach that was taken to performing the viability assessment together with any other background&#xD;
    information. This includes items such as:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Date and location of the review&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Context of the assessment (part of a QA, by invitation from the client etc)&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Formal vs. informal&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        What individuals, groups, departments were interviewed&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        What phase the assessment was performed in&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        What documentation was provided for the assessment&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>2.&amp;nbsp;General Findings and Recommendations&lt;/strong>&lt;br />&#xD;
    This section summarizes the assessment's major findings and recommendations.&amp;nbsp; Documentation should be brief and&#xD;
    actionable, with responsibilities to carry forward recommendations clearly defined.&amp;nbsp; A table or a&#xD;
    header/sub-header organization can be used to present this information. For example:&#xD;
