&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;strong>3.&amp;nbsp;Risk Ranking Worksheet&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    A risk ranking worksheet is a means to prioritize risks during a viability assessment.&amp;nbsp; Not all risks are equally&#xD;
    important.&amp;nbsp; In the General Findings and Recommendations section, the architect will want to focus upon the high&#xD;
    risk/high payback items, and leave reporting lower risks to an appendix or supplemental reading.&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;table bordercolor=&quot;#000000&quot; cellspacing=&quot;0&quot; cellpadding=&quot;0&quot; border=&quot;1&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;tbody>&#xD;
        &lt;tr bgcolor=&quot;#CCCCCC&quot;>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;120&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;strong>Risk&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;120&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;strong>Probability&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;120&quot;>&#xD;
                &lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
                    &lt;strong>Impact&lt;/strong>&#xD;
                &lt;/p>&#xD;
            &lt;/td>&#xD;
            &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot; width=&quot;120&quot;>&#xD;
